             <p id="Overview" style="font-family: 'Book Antiqua'; font-size: x-large; font-weight: bolder; font-style: inherit; font-variant: normal; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-decoration: underline">OVERVIEW  
<h3 style="color: #cc0000">AACHMAN REGENCY SHIMLA</h3>  
Aachman Regency with the wide range of facilities and amenities does make every patron feel at home. The hotel does have immense options for both business and leisure. The resort is tugged with the immense facilities of parking, 24 hour front desk and Wi-Fi amenities are also provided. The management here does courteously take care of every need. The hotel is inviting for leisure, recreation or business purpose. The team here does has takes care for every needs.        

<h3 style="color: #cc0000">HOTEL WILLOW BANKS</h3>  
Hotel Willow Banks Shimla was constructed in the year 1871 and is situated on the mall road. This was originally owned by Arthur James Craddok who is the “Architect and Builder of Shimla”. Later, this was redesigned into a Heritage Hotel with all modern amenities and at affordable rates. The hotel is also rated by Trip Advisor as one of the “Top 10 Jewel Hotels of India” and has also received “Bravo” badge from Trip Advisor. The hotel offers four kinds of accommodation to the guests which are Deluxe Rooms, Super Deluxe Rooms, Premium Rooms and Suites. To serve the guests with gastronomical delights, the hotel has a multi-cuisine restaurant, a self-service fast food outlet and a pub to relax. The hotel has a Billiard Table, Pool Table, Health Club & Beauty Parlor, steam, sauna, Jacuzzi, table tennis, cyber café, Gym and rejuvenating Kerala Ayurvedic massage. The hotel also has a banquet hall that can be used for conferences, weddings, parties, etc. The hotel also arranges for River rafting, trekking, sightseeing and picnics. The hotel is ideal for both business and leisure travelers.

<h3 style="color: #cc0000">SOLANG VALLEY RESORT</h3>  
Solang Valley is nestled amidst the tranquil beauty and peace of Manali. The hotel is a sprawling property located away from the daily hustle bustle of the city’s center. The hotel is located 60 km from Bhuntar airport and 12 km from Manali Bus stand. Major destinations like Tibetan Monastery, Hadimba temple, Manu temple and Shiva Temple lie in close proximity.
The hotel’s health club is a great place to get some exercises done while observing the beauty lying outside the wide windows. A conference hall is present on premises to meet all your business needs. Many facilities are offered by the hotel that includes indoor/outdoor game equipment, skating rink, basket ball court, travel desk, Wi-Fi connectivity, laundry and parking on site. Shop for souvenirs in the hotel’s shopping arcade or enjoy a quite walk around the gardens. The hotel’s surroundings are perfect for adventure sports like paragliding and skiing and can be easily organized by the hotel’s staff. The hotel’s rooms are categorized into deluxe rooms, Superior rooms, Maharaja Suites and Presidential suites.The dining options include The Gazebo, which serves Italian, Dhaam that serves multi-cuisine and Little Malana that is a bar-cum-discotheque. 

<h3 style="color: #cc0000">SPAN RESORT</h3>  
The sound of the water greets the guests as they explore the 10 acres that Span Resort is spread over. The sprawling resort is a place to seek tranquility and a harmony with the gods in the valley that promises a memorable beauty.
The hotel’s swimming pool is a great place to unwind and go for a lazy swim on a sunny day. All your rejuvenation needs meet their destination in the hotel’s La Riviere Spa by L’Occitane. The hotel’s spa uses locally grown herbs and river bed stones to give award winning therapies and treatment for the perfect balance of mind, body and soul. A conference hall is present with state-of-the-art equipment for all your business needs. For the health conscious guests a health club is also located inside the hotel.  Create beautiful memories as the hotel serves as a wedding venue and leaves no stone unturned in turning it into a dream wedding.  The hotel’s personal charter aircraft SpanAir has been providing safe flights since 1995 and can easily be booked for private needs. Other facilities offered at the hotel include airport transfer (chargeable), babysitting, bicycle rental, travel desk, business center, special arrangements for differently abled guests, safety deposit boxes, laundry service & dry cleaning, indoor/outdoor games, golf course, children’s park, souvenir shop and Wi-Fi connectivity. The hotel’s 36 elegantly appointed rooms are a luxury to stay in.
The dining and bar options include Zensation, walk around the world, pool bar, bar, library lounge and café and riverside restaurant. The hotel is the recipient of Certificate of Excellence for the year 2014 from TripAdvisor.

<h3 style="color: #cc0000">HOTEL SITARA INTERNATIONAL</h3> 
Established in 2001, Hotel Sitara International is a 3 star hotel that offers a perfect blend of excellent location, contemporary facilities and hospitality. The hotel is approximately 49 km from the Bhuntar Airport and less than 1 km from the Manali bus station. Staying here offers a great opportunity for the globe trotters as the hotel has major tourist spots in its vicinity namely Tibetan Monastery, Vashist Hot Springs, Nehru Kund, Hidimba Temple, Naggar Castle, Arjun Cave, and Nicholas Roerich Art Gallery. The marketplace, known as The Mall, is just about 1.2 km away. The hotel provides numerous state-of-the-art facilities and conveniences such as laundry and dry cleaning facilities, currency exchange, E.P.A.B.X., travel desk, doctor on call, car parking and safety deposit lockers. Recreational facilities include children’s playground, games rooms, discotheque and a well equipped gym. The hotel arranges for sightseeing in and around the town as per the guests’ requirements. Adventure sports including trekking, jeep safari, mountain biking, river rafting and paragliding, etc. are also organized by the hotel on request. 

